The paper proposes a transfer framework for reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper focuses on the use of value function representations and policy improvement operations, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments involve navigation tasks and control of a robotic arm, which are typical applications in the sub-categories of cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of computer vision techniques for the robotic arm control task, which suggests a possible connection to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
